25|$|Afghanistan {{adopted a}} new {{constitution}} in January 2004, establishing the country as an Islamic Republic. According to the constitution, the Afghan government consists of a President, two Vice Presidents, and a National Assembly (Parliament). The National Assembly has two houses: the House of People (Wolesi Jirga), and the House of Elders (<b>Meshrano</b> <b>Jirga).</b> There is also an independent Judiciary branch consisting of the Supreme Court (Stara Mahkama), High Courts and Appeal Courts. The President appoints {{the members of the}} Supreme Court with the approval of the Wolesi Jirga.|$|E
